#MEM id=triple-pass-protocol source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Technical/raj/skills/operating-system/triple-pass-protocol/SKILL.md savings=9%
M||tx|---
M||name|triple-pass-protocol
M||desc|rj's pre-delivery validation gate. Three passes — Audit, Adversarial Critique, Fix — before any rt is marked ready for dv rv or QA.
M||vers|1.0.0
M||tx|---
M|Purp|tx|A rt shipped w/o internal challenge is a rt w/ unchecked assumptions. This protocol forces rj to audit his own implementation before it reaches dv or qn — catching missing auth checks, unvalidated inputs, and wrong status codes before they become production vulnerabilities.
M|Purp|tx|---
M|Pass|tx|rv the rt implementation against rj's full checklist. Name every issue found, where it appears, and what it breaks. Draft the status (IMPLEMENTED / blk) and any corrections needed.
M|Pass|Stop|
M|Pass|**Ro|**
M|Pass|it|Is all request input parsed through a Zod sc? Any `any` casting or unvalidated data?
M|Pass|it|Does unauthenticated access return `401` — not `500`, not `200`?
M|Pass|it|Are all ap keys accessed via `process.env` server-side only?
M|Pass|- If|is `CRON_SECRET` validated as the FIRST line before ANY handler code?
M|Pass|**Sc|**
M|Pass|it|Does this rt mutate data in sb? Has dv reviewed and approved the sc?
M|Pass|it|Is RLS enabled on every table this rt touches? Is there a venture_slug or auth.uid() policy?
M|Pass|it|Are queries parameterized — zero string interpolation?
M|Pass|**Er|**
M|Pass|it|Does every code branch have a try/catch?
M|Pass|- Ar|400, 401, 403, 404, 429, 500, 503?
M|Pass|it|Does the er rp body contain only us-safe messages — no stack, no internals, no DB sc?
M|Pass|it|If a dependency (sb, Apify, YouTube) is down — does the rt return 503 + Retry-After, not 500?
M|Pass|**Sc|**
M|Pass|it|Am I implementing exactly what dv's ap contract specifies?
M|Pass|it|Did I deviate from the contract w/o dv approval?
M|Pass|it|Does my rp shape match exactly what mi expects from dv's MEMORY.md?
M|Pass|**Ve|**
M|Pass|it|Is blk for a real sec/architecture issue — or am I over-weighting a style concern?
M|Pass|it|Is IMPLEMENTED confident enough? wld I stand behind this rt in a sec rv?
M|Pass|tx|Revise anything the critique found. Correct status codes, add missing Zod schemas, fix er rp. Then mark ready for dv rv + QA.
M|Pass|tx|---
M|Outp|tx|dv and qn see the Pass 3 output only. Never narrate the triple-pass process.
M|Outp|Stat|
M|Outp|tx|```
M|Outp|rt|/ap/[name] — IMPLEMENTED / blk
M|Outp|Sche|[yes — dv reviewed / no change]
M|Outp|Cont|[dv MEMORY.md date]
M|Outp|QA h|endpoint [URL], tst w/ [payload]
M|Outp|tx|```